Step by step Chicago Map 12

The map is an essential piece of our dashboard

One of the requirements was to see the location where the Most Violent Crime happens 

1 â€“ create a master dimension with the community name and zipCode 


2- drag a chart object map and drop it on the sheet

 3- drag and drop the ZipCommunity DD master dimension as area layer.

4- Qualified the location by (Country, Administration levels as need to scope the location)

 

5- In layer display   custom visible drill down level to zip_code only by unselecting  community name

 6- color the map base on the expression

If( $(vViolentCrime%) < $(vAvgVCrime) and Count({$<[Arrest] = {'fales'}>} [Arrest]) /Count( Violent)< $(vUSC)  , Green(),

If( $(vViolentCrime%) < $(vAvgVCrime) and Count({$<[Arrest] = {'false'}>} [Arrest]) /Count( Violent)> $(vUSC)  ,Yellow(),

If( $(vViolentCrime%) > $(vAvgVCrime) and Count({$<[Arrest] = {'false'}>} [Arrest]) /Count( Violent)< $(vUSC)  ,'Orange',

If( $(vViolentCrime%) > $(vAvgVCrime) and Count({$<[Arrest] = {'false'}>} [Arrest]) /Count( Violent)> $(vUSC)  ,Red()))))



7- repeat steps 2 to 6 to create a point layer to display the community name on step 3 choose point layer instead of Area layer.  on step 5 In layer display custom visible drill down a level to community name only by unselecting zip Code



Final Result 

 

This article explains the safest neighborhoods in Chicago
